  "doc_id": "22879",
  "text": "Fix an additive character ψ : K\\A → C × . A primary tool in the study of the representation theory of Mp(W ) has been the theta correspondence, utilizing the classical oscillator representation ω ψ . For example, such liftings were recently used by Gan-Ichino to extend the notion of Arthur parameter to Mp(W ) A [CITATION_1] . Motivated by the work of Bump-Friedberg-Ginzburg [CITATION_2] , one may attempt to study generalizations of theta liftings on BD-covering groups in the hope of gaining insight into the representation theory of higher degree covers.",
  "correct_citation": {
